abstract: The president’s lawyer said the House managers had failed to prove him guilty “beyond a reasonable doubt.”
snippet: The president’s lawyer said the House managers had failed to prove him guilty “beyond a reasonable doubt.”
lead_paragraph: In order to convict President Trump, the Senate must find him guilty “beyond a reasonable doubt,” a lawyer for Mr. Trump, Patrick Philbin, told the Senate.
headline_main: Trump lawyer invents a standard of proof for impeachment.
byline_original: By Sheryl Gay Stolberg and Charlie Savage

abstract: “If his staffers disagree with him, that does not mean that he is doing something wrong,” said Patrick Philbin, an attorney for President Trump.
snippet: “If his staffers disagree with him, that does not mean that he is doing something wrong,” said Patrick Philbin, an attorney for President Trump.
lead_paragraph: Responding to a question from Senator Mike Lee, Republican of Utah, the president’s defense team sought to frame the Democratic impeachment managers’ case as one “based on a policy difference” between President Trump and the career diplomats who sounded the alarm on his pressure campaign on Ukraine.

headline_main: The president can’t defy his foreign policy because he sets it, his lawyer argues.

abstract: President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed a new North American trade agreement during an outdoor ceremony at the White House attended by about 400 guests - but not the key Democrats who helped secure congressional passage of the deal.
snippet: President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed a new North American trade agreement during an outdoor ceremony at the White House attended by about 400 guests - but not the key Democrats who helped secure congressional passage of the deal.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump on Wednesday signed a new North American trade agreement during an outdoor ceremony at the White House attended by about 400 guests - but not the key Democrats who helped secure congressional passage of the deal.
headline_main: Trump Signs USMCA,' Ending the NAFTA Nightmare'; Key Democrats Not Invited
headline_print_headline: Trump Signs USMCA,' Ending the NAFTA Nightmare'; Key Democrats Not Invited

abstract: The Palestinians have furiously rejected President Donald Trump's Mideast plan that would grant them limited autonomy in parts of the West Bank, while allowing Israel to annex all its settlements there and keep nearly all of east Jerusalem.
snippet: The Palestinians have furiously rejected President Donald Trump's Mideast plan that would grant them limited autonomy in parts of the West Bank, while allowing Israel to annex all its settlements there and keep nearly all of east Jerusalem.
lead_paragraph: AL-KASSARAT, West Bank — The Palestinians have furiously rejected President Donald Trump's Mideast plan that would grant them limited autonomy in parts of the West Bank, while allowing Israel to annex all its settlements there and keep nearly all of east Jerusalem.
headline_main: Angry Palestinians Face Dilemma in Responding to Trump Plan
headline_print_headline: Angry Palestinians Face Dilemma in Responding to Trump Plan

abstract: The Federal Reserve kept its key interest rate unchanged at a low level Wednesday amid an economy that looks solid but faces potential global threats, including from China’s viral outbreak.
snippet: The Federal Reserve kept its key interest rate unchanged at a low level Wednesday amid an economy that looks solid but faces potential global threats, including from China’s viral outbreak.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve kept its key interest rate unchanged at a low level Wednesday amid an economy that looks solid but faces potential global threats, including from China’s viral outbreak.
headline_main: Fed Leaves Key Rate Unchanged at Low Level Amid Global Risks
headline_print_headline: Fed Leaves Key Rate Unchanged at Low Level Amid Global Risks

abstract: The central bank suggested it would remain patient after cutting rates three times in 2019.
snippet: The central bank suggested it would remain patient after cutting rates three times in 2019.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Federal Reserve officials left interest rates unchanged at their first meeting of 2020 on Wednesday, upholding their patient stance after an active, and often tumultuous, 2019.

abstract: “There is in fact overwhelming evidence that the president withheld the military aid directly to get a personal political benefit,” Jason Crow of Colorado, one of the managers, said.
snippet: “There is in fact overwhelming evidence that the president withheld the military aid directly to get a personal political benefit,” Jason Crow of Colorado, one of the managers, said.
lead_paragraph: House managers used a question from Senator Dianne Feinstein, Democrat of California, to reiterate the heart of their case: accusing President Trump’s lawyers of incorrectly stating that there is no evidence that Mr. Trump linked security assistance to investigations.
headline_main: House managers use question from Feinstein to restate their case.

abstract: Representative Adam Schiff replied that there was no question that President Trump was motivated by personal political gain and used that to argue to hear additional witnesses.
snippet: Representative Adam Schiff replied that there was no question that President Trump was motivated by personal political gain and used that to argue to hear additional witnesses.
lead_paragraph: Democrats began their questioning on Wednesday by asking House managers about revelations from an upcoming book by John R. Bolton, the former national security adviser, giving the manager an open-ended opportunity to push for additional witnesses and documents. Representative Adam B. Schiff, the lead manager, quickly referred to the previous question from three Republican senators, who had asked White House lawyers about what to do if they conclude President Trump had multiple motivations for his actions.

abstract: The U.S. Federal Reserve is expected to keep interest rates unchanged when it wraps up its first policy meeting of the year on Wednesday.
